cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "PMSM Control Claude Skills (for MATLAB/Simulink): A Methodology and Skill Library for AI-Augmented PMSM Simulink Modeling"
message: "If you use this software, please cite it using the metadata below."
type: software
version: 1.0.5
date-released: 2026-05-20
license: Apache-2.0
repository-code: "https://github.com/calebzu/pmsm-control-claude-skills-for-matlab"
authors:
  - family-names: Zong
    given-names: Chuhang
    affiliation: "School of Electrical and Electronic Engineering, Nanyang Technological University"
    email: ZONG0008@e.ntu.edu.sg
abstract: >
  A methodology and skill library for AI-augmented MATLAB/Simulink modeling
  of Permanent Magnet Synchronous Motor (PMSM) control, designed for use
  with Anthropic's Claude Code agent system. Includes four skill artifacts
  (motor-pmsm-base, motor-fcs-mpc, motor-dtc-pmsm, motor-smc-pmsm) validated
  across three control methodology families (FCS-MPC, DTC, SMC) under
  anti-contamination and anti-cheating discipline, accompanied by an
  11-phase Reference Model Learning Workflow.
keywords:
  - PMSM
  - permanent magnet synchronous motor
  - motor control
  - field-oriented control
  - direct torque control
  - sliding mode control
  - model predictive control
  - MATLAB
  - Simulink
  - Claude Code
  - large language model
  - LLM agent
  - AI-augmented engineering simulation
  - methodology
  - reproducibility
